define a function to test cointegration

jtest = function(t1.name, t2.name, df) {
  df = df[which(df$id %in% c(t1.name,t2.name)),]
  df = spread(df,id,logprice)
  df = df[complete.cases(df),]
  ts = df[,c(2,3)]
  j = summary(ca.jo(ts))
  r = data.frame(stock1 = t1.name, stock2 = t2.name, 
                 stat = j@teststat[2])
  r[, c("pct10", "pct5", "pct1")] = j@cval[2, ]
  return(r)
}

calculate rets and cumrets

goodpair = goodpair %>% arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(lag.signal = dplyr::lag(signal,1),
         ret.buy.y = spread-dplyr::lag(spread,1)) %>%
  mutate(ret.signal = lag.signal*ret.buy.y) %>%
  na.omit() %>% mutate(cumret = cumsum(ret.signal))
plot(goodpair$cumret~goodpair$date,type='l')
